{"word":"H1803 - דַּלָּה - dallâh - dal-law' - Hair","slug":"H1803","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דַּלָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dallâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>dal-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hair"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05BC;&#x05D4; - dalla&#x0302;h</b> - <i>dal-law'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H1802\">H1802</a>; properly something <i>dangling</i>, that is, a loose <i>thread</i> or <i>hair</i>; figuratively <i>indigent: - </i>hair, pining sickness, poor (-est sort)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1800\">H1800</a>, <a href=\"#/H1807\">H1807</a>, <a href=\"#/H1809\">H1809</a>, <a href=\"#/H1810\">H1810</a>"}]}